  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study hypotheses is that the introduction of dose escalated treosulfan, in substitution
      to busulfan or melphalan, will reduce toxicity after allogeneic transplantation while
      improving disease eradication in patients with lymphoid malignancies not eligible for
      standard transplantation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
